Package: ccml
Type: Package
Title: A R Protocol for Consensus Clustering of Multiple Predictive
        Labels with Different Sample Coverage
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Chuanxing", family = "Li", email = "chuan-xing.li@ki.se", role = c("aut", "cre")),
  person(given = "Meng", family = "Zhou", email="zhoumeng@wmu.edu.cn", role="aut"))
Description: Consensus clustering, also called meta-clustering or cluster ensembles has been increasing used in clinical data. Current consensus clustering methods tend to ensemble a number of different clusterings
    from mathematical replicates with similar sample coverage. As the fact of commonly variety
    of sample coverage in the real-world data, a new consensus clustering strategy dealing with
    such biological replicates is required. This is a two-step consensus clustering R package, which
    is used to input multiple predictive labels with different sample coverage (missing labels).
